In [ ]:
res = {}
for instance_name, instance_grades in grades.items():
    res[instance_name] = {}
    for method_name, grade in instance_grades.items():
        meth_name = method_name.value.replace("_", " ").title()
        res[instance_name][meth_name] = [grade.avg, grade.min, grade.max, *grade.runtime]
In [ ]:
dfs = {}
for instance, methods in res.items():
    df = (
        pd.DataFrame.from_dict(
            methods,
            orient="index",
            columns=["Average Score", "Min Score", "Max Score", "Total runtime", "Per run runtime"],
        )
        .reset_index()
        .sort_values(by="Min Score")
        .reset_index(drop=True)
    )
    df.columns = [
        "Method",
        "Average Score",
        "Min Score",
        "Max Score",
        "Total runtime",
        "Per run runtime",
    ]
    df.index.name = instance
    dfs[instance] = df

Summary:¶

Parameters for iterative local search:

  • max_runtime: 105s (average runtime per run for MSLS method)
  • basline: local search with delta moves
  • perturbation: Inter node exchange (random 4 out with random 4 in)

Number of runs until the stopping condition is met was around 1200 (stopping condition 105s).

We can see that Local Search Iterative method gives us best results. MSLS while worse can be clearly seen as an improved version of its used baseline (Local search with delta moves).
